HEADWORD: Disestablish
<hw>Dis`es*tab"lish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
unsettle; to break up (anything established); to deprive, as a church,
of its connection with the state.</def> <rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

